## 2. Goals & Non-Goals\
\
### 2.1 Goals\
\
1. **Deliver working experience in \uc0\u8804  1 calendar week of focused development time**  \
   - Core E2E flow: crash \uc0\u8594  damage data \u8594  repair estimate \u8594  dealer selection \u8594  \'93appointment\'94.\
2. **Demonstrate \'93new way of building\'94**  \
   - Single lean PO/architect (Jefin) directing multiple AI agents to build the product.  \
   - Minimal manual coding; heavy use of Cloud Code, Opus 4.5, Copilot, etc.\
3. **Create a \'93jaw-dropping\'94 demo for dealers**  \
   - Fun, visually compelling, clear story: \'93You crashed your car, here\'92s what it costs, here\'92s how VW dealers take care of you.\'94\
4. **Lay groundwork for real business value**  \
   - Design so that inventory optimization and real dealer/parts integration can be layered in.\
   - Capture architecture and domain knowledge (ontologies, knowledge graphs, episodic memory) in repo/docs.\
\
### 2.2 Non-Goals (for this phase)\
\
- Real-time, per-millisecond damage/price updates during the race.\
- Full production hardening (SLA, HA, full security review, etc.).\
- Full integration into Palantir (must run **outside** Palantir due to licensing).\
- Complete and accurate coverage of all VW models, all dealers, all parts.\
- Deep financial or SAP/ERP integration.\
