## 3. Users & Use Cases\
\
### 3.1 Primary Users\
\
1. **Dealer Event Attendees (Drivers)**  \
   - VW dealer representatives attending Brand Day.\
   - Use the simulator, crash cars, and see repair estimates.\
\
2. **VW Marketing & Event Staff**  \
   - Operate the experience during the event.\
   - Use big screen to tell the story to the room.\
\
3. **VW Business Stakeholders (e.g., Lucas)**  \
   - Evaluate Object Edge capabilities.\
   - Look for how this could map to real business problems.\
\
4. **Object Edge Internal Stakeholders (Valmor, Rene, Diego, etc.)**  \
   - Support the demo at the event.\
   - Demonstrate AE/consulting capability on top of the demo.\
\
### 3.2 Key Use Cases\
\
1. **UC1: Dealer Drives & Crashes a Car**\
   - User selects a VW model in BeamNG (e.g., T-Cross, Golf).\
   - Drives a race session, inevitably crashes into obstacles or other cars.\
   - Finishes the race.\
\
2. **UC2: \'93Repair My Car\'94**\
   - After race completion, driver presses \'93Repair my car\'94 (inside game or via adjacent UI).\
   - System captures crash/damage telemetry from BeamNG (e.g., via API, CSV export, or memory/snoop mechanism).\
   - System infers which parts are damaged and to what extent.\
\
3. **UC3: Repair Estimate Generation**\
   - Back-end maps damage \uc0\u8594  VW part numbers / part descriptions.\
   - System computes repair cost (parts + optionally labor).\
   - Generates an invoice-like summary.\
\
4. **UC4: Dealer Selection**\
   - UI displays:\
     - Damaged areas.\
     - Required parts list.\
     - Estimated total repair cost.\
   - User selects a dealer from a list (real or simulated VW dealers near the event city).\
\
5. **UC5: \'93Appointment\'94 Creation**\
   - System pretends to schedule an appointment with chosen dealer.\
   - Shows confirmation screen: dealer name, estimated cost, \'93appointment date/time\'94 (stubbed).\
   - Optionally \'93sends\'94 invoice (e.g., simulated email or on-screen confirmation).\
\
6. **UC6: Big-Screen Storytelling**\
   - Event host mirrors the experience on a large screen:\
     - Race/crash sequence.\
     - Transition to repair app UX.\
     - Visual walkthrough of damage, cost, dealer selection, and \'93inventory optimization\'94.\
\
7. **UC7 (Stretch): Inventory Optimization Story**\
   - System checks dealer\'92s (stubbed) inventory for required parts.\
   - If some parts are missing, shows:\
     - \'93Dealer A is missing 3 parts; proposing transfer from Dealer B/C.\'94\
   - Visual narrative of routing parts across the dealer network.\
