## 4. Functional Requirements\
\
### 4.1 BeamNG Integration\
\
**FR-1** \'96 BeamNG Environment Setup  \
- Install and run BeamNG locally on a dedicated event machine.  \
- Ensure at least 2\'963 VW models are available:\
  - T-Cross\
  - Golf\
  - (Optional) Additional VW models if available with minimal extra work.\
\
**FR-2** \'96 Telemetry Extraction  \
- Ability to capture crash/damage data for a completed race. Options (any viable approach is acceptable):\
  - **Preferred:** Use any official/unofficial BeamNG APIs to access:\
    - Per-part damage metrics (panels, suspension, engine, etc.).\
    - Crash event metadata (speed at impact, angle, location on vehicle).\
  - **Fallback 1:** Use existing plugin/module Fernando tested:\
    - On \'93end race\'94 or \'93repair my car\'94, export a CSV file with damage/telemetry.\
  - **Fallback 2:** Use system cache/memory scraping or similar reverse engineering (as discovered via Claude or Copilot) to extract damage state.\
\
**FR-3** \'96 Triggering the Export  \
- Must be able to trigger telemetry export **after the race** (not real time).  \
- Ideal trigger: custom \'93Repair my car\'94 button in-game or adjacent UI that signals the export step.\
\
### 4.2 Damage Interpretation & Parts Mapping\
\
**FR-4** \'96 Damage Parsing Module  \
- Parse the BeamNG output (API or CSV) into a normalized internal format:\
  - Damaged components (e.g., front bumper, left fender, suspension, windshield).\
  - Damage severity/intensity per component.\
  - Car model ID and configuration.\
\
**FR-5** \'96 Parts Ontology / Knowledge Base  \
- Define a simple ontology / mapping for VW car models:\
  - Car Model \uc0\u8594  Assemblies \u8594  Parts (with IDs, names, categories).\
- Use either:\
  - Real VW parts data from GCP (via Rene/Jags if feasible), or\
  - Synthetic dataset with realistic structure and naming.\
\
**FR-6** \'96 Damage-to-Parts Logic  \
- For each damaged component, determine:\
  - Which parts must be replaced vs. repaired.\
  - Quantities (usually 1 per part but flexible).\
- Provide a confidence level for mapping (for potential future tuning).\
\
### 4.3 Pricing & Invoice Generation\
\
**FR-7** \'96 Pricing Data  \
- Attach a price to each part:\
  - Real prices from VW data if available, otherwise simulated prices in realistic ranges.\
- Optional: define labor cost multipliers (per component or per hour).\
\
**FR-8** \'96 Estimate Calculation  \
- Compute:\
  - Parts subtotal.\
  - Optional labor subtotal.\
  - Total estimated repair cost.\
- Apply tax or fees if required for realism (configurable).\
\
**FR-9** \'96 Invoice Object  \
- Generate a structured \'93Invoice\'94 object containing:\
  - Vehicle model & run ID.\
  - List of damaged components.\
  - List of parts (ID, name, quantity, unit price, line total).\
  - Totals (parts, labor, grand total).\
  - Timestamp.\
  - Dealer selection status (pending/assigned).\
\
### 4.4 Dealer & Inventory Logic\
\
**FR-10** \'96 Dealer Directory  \
- Maintain a list of dealers (focus on Brazil, ideally S\'e3o Paulo / Rio):\
  - Dealer ID, name, city, basic contact info.\
- Support a small subset of real or stub dealers attending the event.\
\
**FR-11** \'96 Dealer Inventory (Stub)  \
- For each dealer, maintain simulated inventory:\
  - Part ID, on-hand quantity.\
- Inventory dataset can be static JSON or seeded from sample data.\
\
**FR-12** \'96 Dealer Selection Flow  \
- Allow user to:\
  - Filter or show dealers near a given location (basic filtering is enough).\
  - Select one dealer to handle the repair.\
- Once dealer selected, associate invoice with dealer record.\
\
**FR-13 (Stretch)** \'96 Inventory Check & Optimization  \
- For chosen dealer:\
  - Identify which parts are in-stock vs. missing.\
- If missing:\
  - Show a simple optimization suggestion:\
    - \'93We found missing part X at Dealer B, Y at Dealer C; estimated transfer can complete by [date].\'94\
- Visualization can be simple (e.g., table or mini-map) but should tell a compelling story.\
\
