## 6. Technical Approach\
\
### 6.1 Stack\
\
- **Core Development:**\
  - Cloud Code CLI (Claude Code).\
  - Opus 4.5 Max plan (Anthropic).\
  - GitHub Copilot as optional assistant inside VS Code.\
\
- **Runtime / Hosting:**\
  - Initial plan: **local hosting** on event machine (no strict need for cloud deployment).\
  - Optionally: Dockerize and deploy to GCP (Cloud Run or similar) if time allows.\
\
- **Language & Frameworks (proposed, can be adjusted by AI-assisted design):**\
  - Backend: Node.js/TypeScript or Python (choose based on AI plan and dev comfort).\
  - Frontend: React or simple SPA framework (minimize complexity; prioritize speed).\
\
### 6.2 AI-Driven Development Paradigm\
\
- Jefin acts as:\
  - Product Owner.\
  - Architect.\
  - AI \'93team lead\'94.\
- Development pattern:\
  - Use AI agents to:\
    - Generate initial architecture and scaffolding.\
    - Generate and refine modules (BeamNG integration, mapping, UI).\
    - Maintain documentation files.\
  - Minimize hand-written code; focus on:\
    - Requirements.\
    - Architecture decisions.\
    - Reviewing and steering AI-generated code.\
\
### 6.3 Knowledge & Memory Structures (Internal)\
\
- While full ontologies/knowledge graphs are not mandatory for MVP, design to align with:\
  - **Ontologies/Knowledge Graphs**: parts, models, dealers, inventories.\
  - **Entity Dossiers**: cars, dealers, invoices as structured entities.\
  - **Episodic Memory**: each race/repair session logged with key facts (for future analytics/features).\
